headline: 1 Semiconductor Stock on Our Buy List and 2 to Avoid
summary: Semiconductors are the core infrastructure powering the Information Age. Demand for chips is variable though, meaning that corporate inventory levels and sentiment can significantly impact the industry. The market doesn’t seem convinced we’re due for another upturn as the sector’s 3.1% gain over the past six months has trailed the S&P 500 by 2 percentage points.
